White House spokesman Josh Earnest said today that the president believes 'to deny the existence of climate change is to deny an observable fact that is substantiated by science' He was responding to a question about a Duke study that said the earth isn't warming as fast as previously thought . 
  Obama mocked opponents of global warming on Earth Day and said it is 'a problem now' He said 'there are some who deny that fact because it might be inconvenient to their strongest political supporters'